costbench bundled quality-priors — sourcing & licenses
======================================================

The seed quality priors in src/costbench/models.yaml currently ship as
ILLUSTRATIVE PLACEHOLDER values: they are synthetic, not measured, and are not
attributed to any source. Nothing in this repo is republished from a benchmark
result table, and no Artificial Analysis data is bundled (see docs/PRIORS.md).

When the placeholders are replaced with real numbers, each value must come from
a source that actually states it and must carry that source's license. Likely
sources and their licenses:

HumanEval (benchmark definition)
  Repo:    https://github.com/openai/human-eval
  License: MIT
  Note:    defines the task; does NOT publish per-model scores. Cite a
           leaderboard or system card that states the score, not this repo.

MMLU-Pro (benchmark definition)
  Repo:    https://github.com/TIGER-AI-Lab/MMLU-Pro
  License: MIT
  Note:    same as above — definition only, not a model-score table.

Provider system cards / benchmark leaderboards
  A real per-model number must be quoted from a source URL that contains it,
  cited row-by-row in models.yaml with the date it was verified.

NOTE: models.yaml priors section is SEED DATA. Priors are a starting point, not ground truth —
the only ground truth is your own `costbench run`.
